* git version => to see if you have already installed git.
- git config -- global user.name ""
- git config -- global user.email""
=> to connect local repo and remote repo. 
- git config --list => to see if it connected. 

1. Git Init 
* create a local Repo in your own PC. 
=> git init

* link the local repository to an empty Github repository 
=> git remote add origin [GitHub-repo-URL]

2. Git clone
Clone (táº£i) a remote repo on GitHub to Local PC 
=> git clone [GitHub_Repo_URL]

* GIT Workflow: 
Working directory ---- git init ----> initialization ---- git add ---
---> stagging Area  ----- git commit ----> Local repository ---------
-- git push ----> git hub

3. Git Add
*Add changes to Staging Area
=> git add file

4. Git commit
*Snapshot the file in preparation for versioning 
=> git commit -m "descriptive message"

=> git commit --amend -m "amend descriptive message"

5. Git push
*Uploads all local branch commits to Github
=> git push origin [branch-name]